infos.info: (1) Mostly sustained. - (2) Broadcast from New York (1951-1954) - (3) Broadcast from Hollywood (1954-1955) - (4) Referenced as Barry Crane in ' Radio's Golden Years' - (5) For William Gargan, who had originated the better known Martin Kane character, it was an interesting bit of type-casting. As a young man he had worked in a real detective office and had once confessed amusement at the blunders of radio detectives. - (6) Himan Brown directed in New York, Arthur Jacobson directed in Hollywood.
